[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering new features**\n\nI'm thinking about adding a functional feature that isn't currently covered. Existing aspects include URI, model, headers, form, marshalling, multipart, routing, and SSE settings. I want to ensure any public API is natively safe under 60. It seems like I only need to modify the test file. \n\nOne potential feature could be the Http().singleRequest for client/server binding, which is heavier but okay for close resources. Alternatively, WebSocket could allow for dynamism, but I want to avoid hitting the server unnecessarily. Also, I've noticed some areas like content coders and gzip might not be fully covered, so it’s essential to ensure the new feature is functionally meaningful while understanding the dependencies.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0d61b082236e73200169facadc136881a2ac65e4969a7d1195\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-srgJUX-b_BIRbz8qNHrlXs47azhT79nrv74ycNdl_O18ADF_2ySZU9FyHxiwO_Jl9CsYoPlj2c6AtlNOktGG7WMVyl8fW2s8RtDmBE9iTj9AY1QQM2xyFFQdt-gYzxH5qGjN5RIWge6GQtPTFboEI5SclM9odweM8XE05UC0RSSAzXPgSEnBdkiTzw3WHinNpg5JCSs--I1DRIl608oNbhBT66jPy6qObEOzK_riBawk4kIpMf0glQZAU6nVGrGEg3rr6ledU3UoOaGUA9ZAN_UgEV5Hn2a9dITiAkU7evH57H5MdPF228q0_Nyornn-LVA9xihxquBx-gYBRzTetdD71khI6Pimj0QD4Z4VUjMljoirmoCnM_bj7H74LYJzpCWgixkWU1tU5BM-6Tihhwn2p_N6_vcho-i5-S0ESaD1JOIq8Tdr-RWZTB4Z9RuR1tZp0A_4R5yGbHUrJ5068EH4PUVSn_AJZE5iHP8zmBJcBnXboG__303vigRd7hbNKlu9m7XJTFOI1ioJqcZfANpRUBlB7zKtNQ65-SxAqXNuuUkqxwy6b0U9_L9g48xDbpvCfEFAY1Epu08t_YJx-gtMRHAa_-F8zxULonpN9a_tpAnrxl9Efu8BGoWTd0yKASrXUlMB9z8RwUed9Ge2io_eJxmPRFGS7QwZfGvIcyVYadAUaTWUclCKv_H2AZPnuGq4CaX-A_NJfcmO_8WbqH76D6tKSkxA43oKzvwYx9jjtmcJVPhvX_JgZ7rF_5_AMtOM0WdZpw_nQ9F99u2s2cNVnIxGL03mXnq5KhOPQlxwHjbKPxx7Sqczo96ncfLG49TBCdmUJBhxKQjyLqxVbCREZLZ_Mg1jam4UY9ai16ox_j5DYrogKYfI0dZtoaGZJXkbka_-_G9tSe_cW1bN7btRgczbS__Fi46HhuC-C2SwNdlsbfcfP_BX80Jrv2JLp0obH96DnsvTW8PgRYGnPJ6a_gJWVx