[tool-call] delta {"path":"tests/src/org.apache.pekko/pekko-http_2.13/1.3.0/src/test/scala/org_apache_pekko/pekko_http_2_13/Pekko_http_2_13Test.scala","edits":[{"oldText":"import org.apache.pekko.http.scaladsl.client.RequestBuilding._\n","newText":"import org.apache.pekko.http.scaladsl.Http\nimport org.apache.pekko.http.scaladsl.client.RequestBuilding._\n"},{"oldText":"  @Test\n  def streamingSupportSettingsAndServerSentEventsExposeExpectedPublicConfiguration(): Unit = {\n","newText":"  @Test\n  def httpServerBindingAndClientRequestsExchangeStrictResponses(): Unit = {\n    withActorSystem(\"pekko-http-server-client\") { implicit system =>\n      implicit val executionContext = system.dispatcher\n\n      val route: Route =\n        path(\"ping\") {\n          get {\n            parameters(\"name\".?(\"anonymous\")) { name =>\n              respondWithHeader(RawHeader(\"X-Service\", \"pekko-http\")) {\n                complete(StatusCodes.OK, s\"pong $name\")\n              }\n            }\n          }\n        }\n\n      val binding = Await.result(Http().newServerAt(\"127.0.0.1\", 0).bind(route), 10.seconds)\n      try {\n        val address = binding.localAddress\n        val response = Await.result(Http().singleRequest(HttpRequest(uri = s\"http://${address.getHostString}:${address.getPort}/ping?name=Apache\")), 10.seconds)\n        val responseEntity = Await.result(response.entity.toStrict(3.seconds), 5.seconds)\n\n        assertEquals(StatusCodes.OK, response.status)\n        assertEquals(Some(\"pekko-http\"), response.header[RawHeader].map(_.value))\n        assertEquals(\"pong Apache\", responseEntity.data.utf8String)\n      } finally {\n        Await.result(binding.unbind(), 10.seconds)\n        Await.result(Http().shutdownAllConnectionPools(), 10.seconds)\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  @Test\n  def streamingSupportSettingsAndServerSentEventsExposeExpectedPublicConfiguration(): Unit = {\n"}]}
[tool-call] end id=call_ehH6ZgcyWszwyHXbOqwfboyY|fc_0d61b082236e73200169facb21eaa881a2adb1aee98444c850 name=edit args={"path": "tests/src/org.apache.pekko/pekko-http_2.13/1.3.0/src/test/scala/org_apache_pekko/pekko_http_2_13/Pekko_http_2_13Test.scala", "edits": [{"oldText": "import org.apache.pekko.http.scaladsl.client.RequestBuilding._\n", "newText": "import org.apache.pekko.http.scaladsl.Http\nimport org.apache.pekko.http.scaladsl.client.RequestBuilding._\n"}, {"oldText": "  @Test\n  def streamingSupportSettingsAndServerSentEventsExposeExpectedPublicConfiguration(): Unit = {\n", "newText": "  @Test\n  def httpServerBindingAndClientRequestsExchangeStrictResponses(): Unit = {\n    withActorSystem(\"pekko-http-server-client\") { implicit system =>\n      implicit val executionContext = system.dispatcher\n\n      val route: Route =\n        path(\"ping\") {\n          get {\n            parameters(\"name\".?(\"anonymous\")) { name =>\n              respondWithHeader(RawHeader(\"X-Service\", \"pekko-http\")) {\n                complete(StatusCodes.OK, s\"pong $name\")\n              }\n            }\n          }\n        }\n\n      val binding = Await.result(Http().newServerAt(\"127.0.0.1\", 0).bind(route), 10.seconds)\n      try {\n        val address = binding.localAddress\n        val response = Await.result(Http().singleRequest(HttpRequest(uri = s\"http://${address.getHostString}:${address.getPort}/ping?name=Apache\")), 10.seconds)\n        val responseEntity = Await.result(response.entity.toStrict(3.seconds), 5.seconds)\n\n        assertEquals(StatusCodes.OK, response.status)\n        assertEquals(Some(\"pekko-http\"), response.header[RawHeader].map(_.value))\n        assertEquals(\"pong Apache\", responseEntity.data.utf8String)\n      } finally {\n        Await.result(binding.unbind(), 10.seconds)\n        Await.result(Http().shutdownAllConnectionPools(), 10.seconds)\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  @Test\n  def streamingSupportSettingsAndServerSentEventsExposeExpectedPublicConfiguration(): Unit = {\n"}]}
[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating authentication features**\n\nI’m considering testing content negotiation with Accept-Encoding, but it seems like the feature isn't fully developed for compression. I’m thinking maybe the server directives are covered, but I'm curious if I should add route authorization. It might strengthen security. However, I'm aware of potential duplicate routes, and the user mentioned not to retest existing flows. For this, I need to verify Credentials and include the authenticateBasic directive, which might lead to a rejection if credentials aren’t valid.\n\n**Exploring testing features**\n\nI’m focused on tests for unauthorized access that include the WWW-Authenticate header. However, this seems to overlap with routing and could lead to duplicate efforts, which isn’t necessarily bad. But I’m cautious since it might interfere with already existing logic flows. I’m considering testing client-side request building with the new server binding, but I need to ensure proper resource cleanup during implementation. For that, I must import necessary libraries, and it seems best to use the existing actor system for this.\n\n**Setting up server binding**\n\nI'm setting up a server binding on localhost and creating a route for handling requests. I have a code snippet to bind the server at a random port and then send a request to a specific URI. I want to see if the response is as expected, but I need to make sure to handle the entity properly by consuming it. Finally, I'll ensure to unbind the server gracefully after testing to avoid leaving any hanging resources.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0d61b082236e73200169facb1153c481a2895ae52929e27293\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-sshQ6tB1R5ZzPiiW_9iZrrCKqFkX7tS6YNS0s5Azu0oHjDC_hIx8mckRP7ASxIFKqZ2vqutrVhiqz-cRAnurzR_Iys7wS1gigj0xt-Kvk_6lxnZAiGb2aXgj9qWEoxTibTknYeN2Q4xaxZOHVU_7qjfdjb-muFiN6BSyu